# Do Not Start the Application

The user runs AMMS.Api only from Visual Studio (F5 / Stop Debugging). Cursor must **never** start the project.

## Forbidden

- `dotnet run` (including `--no-build`, background, or `block_until_ms: 0`)
- Starting `AMMS.Api`, IIS Express, Docker container, or `dotnet watch`
- Any shell command whose primary purpose is to launch the API for testing or verification

## Allowed instead

- `dotnet build` — compile only
- `dotnet test` — run tests without starting the host
- Static code analysis, reading logs the user provides, or explaining how the user can run/debug in VS

## If verification needs a running API

Ask the user to start the project in Visual Studio and share the result (response, log, screenshot). Do not start it yourself.
